<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-297-123  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 297 123.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 16 1989 v10 n3 p36(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Takeovers and mergers dominate '88 stocks.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Nordby, Neil.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Corporate takeovers, leveraged buyouts, and mergers had a majoreffect on communications, hardware, and software industries in1988 and are expected to continue in 1989.andP;  The large number ofsuch transactions were a consequence of the recent stock marketcrash which left many high-tech firms' stock prices lower than theasset value per share and consequently, likely candidates fortakeover.andP;  Other factors affecting the takeover trend includeready availability of leveraged-buyout funds and some firms findit easier and cheaper to take over other companies than develop anew business.andP;  The trend was most evident in the communicationsindustry as reflected in the MIS Week Communications Stock Indexgain of 285.82 points to 1640.60 in 1988.andP;  Several communications,information systems, and software industry takeovers are brieflydescribed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Review of Past YearCommunications IndustryComputer IndustrySoftware PublishersImpact AnalysisTrendsTakeoversMerger.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   1988 stock performance of major communications, hardware, softwarefirms. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>